todayCornerRadius: Defines the corner radius for out of month cells. A value of 0 means that corners are not rounded.
todayFontSize: Defines the font size to be used for the calendar cell that represents the current day, based on the user’s date and time settings.
todayFontColor: Defines the font color to be used for the calendar cell that represents the current day, based on the user’s date and time settings.
todayBorder: Defines the stroke color for strokes outlining the calendar cell that represents the current day, based on the user’s date and time settings.
todayBackground: Defines the fill for the calendar cell that represents the current day, based on the user’s date and time settings.
outOfMonthCornerRadius: Defines the corner radius for few days that show on the current calendar page but are outside the month depicted. A value of 0 means that corners are not rounded.
outOfMonthFontSize: Defines the font size to be used for numbers in out of month cells.
outOfMonthFontColor: Defines the font color to be used for the days that show on the current calendar page but are outside the month depicted. Selected cells style properties take precedence over out of month cell properties.
outOfMonthBorder: Defines the stroke color for strokes outlining the few days that show on the current calendar page but are outside the month depicted.
outOfMonthBackground: Defines the fill for few days that show on the current calendar page but are outside the month depicted.
weekendCornerRadius: Defines the corner radius for weekend cells. A value of 0 means that corners are not rounded.
weekendFontSize: Defines the font size to be used for numbers in weekend cells.
weekendFontColor: Defines the font color to be used for numbers in weekend cells.
weekendBorder: Defines the stroke color for strokes outlining weekend cells.
weekendBackground: Defines the fill for weekend cells.
dowCornerRadius: Defines the corner radius for the cells containing the names of the days of the week. A value of 0 means that corners are not rounded.
dowFontSize: Defines the font size to be used for the names of the days of the week.
dowFontColor: Defines the font color to be used for the names of the days of the week.
dowBorder: Defines the stroke color for strokes outlining the cells that contain the names of the days of the week.
dowBackground: Defines the fill for the cells containing the names of the days of the week.
selectedCornerRadius: Defines the corner radius for selected cells. A value of 0 means that corners are not rounded.
selectedFontSize: Defines the font size for numbers in selected cells.
selectedFontColor: Defines the font color for numbers in selected cells.
selectedBorder: Defines the stroke color for outlining selected cells.
selectedBackground: Defines the fill for selected cells.
normalCornerRadius: Defines the corner radius for weekday cells. A value of 0 means that corners are not rounded.
normalFontSize: Defines the font size for numbers in weekday cells.
normalFontColor: Defines the font color for numbers in weekday cells.
normalBorder: Defines the stroke color for outlining each weekday cell.
normalBackground: Defines the fill for weekday cells.
calendarSpacingHorizontal: Defines the amount of empty space, in pixels, between columns in the calendar.
calendarSpacingVertical: Defines the amount of empty space, in pixels, between rows in the calendar.
calendarPaddingRight: Defines a number of pixels of space between the right edge of the date cells, and the border of the calendar component.
calendarPaddingLeft: Defines a number of pixels of space between the left edge of the date cells, and the border of the calendar component.
calendarPaddingBottom: Defines a number of pixels of space between the bottom edge of the date cells, and the border of the calendar component.
calendarPaddingTop: Defines a number of pixels of space between the top edge of the date cells, and the header of the calendar.
saDir: Defines the direction toward which the series slides. For example, if this property is set to Left, the series slides onto the chart from right to left.
saDurationEx: Defines the duration of the animation in seconds.
markerStrokeStyle: Defines the border stroke style for standard markers.
seriesType:
Defines how the series data is visually represented.

Line series
Markers represent the data points. These markers are connected with lines.

Area series
Markers represent the data points. These markers are connected with lines, and the area delimited by the lines is filled in.

Bar series
Horizontal bars represent the data points.

Column series
Vertical columns represent the data points.
dataTipSymbolId: Specifies the symbol to use as the datatip for the series. This property overrides any text entered in the Datatip property. To use a symbol from this project, enter the name of the symbol. To use a symbol from another project in your library, enter the path to that symbol.
showDataTips: Defines whether datatips are displayed when the user mouses over data points.
markerStrokeWidth: Defines the border stroke weight, in pixels, for standard markers.
markerStroke: Defines the border stroke color for standard markers.
markerFill: Defines the fill for standard markers.
markersType:
Defines the type of markers that represent data points in the series.

None
No markers are used.

Standard
DGLux’s standard marker design is used.

Custom
Create your own marker design as a symbol.
form:
Defines the shape of the lines in a line or area series.

Segment
Markers are connected with line segments.

Step
Markers are connected with orthogonal line segments. Horizontal and vertical segments alternate, beginning with a horizontal segment.

ReverseStep
Data points are connected with orthogonal line segments. Vertical and horizontal segments alternate, beginning with a vertical segment.

Vertical
Only the vertical segments from a Step line form are displayed.

Horizontal
Only the horizontal segments from a Step line form are displayed.

Curve
Markers are connected with a curve.
titleFontSize: Defines the font size used for the month and year text in the calendar header.
divLabels: Defines whether the labels along an axis are coded as <div&#61 elements, thereby allowing multi-line text and HTML tags. By default, labels are rendered as SVG text elements, which are faster but support fewer formatting options.
labelsFontSize: Defines the font size used for the labels along an axis.
tickStrokeWidth: Defines the stroke width of each major tick.
tickStroke: Defines the stroke color of the major ticks.
tickPlacement: Defines whether the major ticks appear on the inside, outside, or center of the line that represents this axis.
tickLength: Defines the length of each major tick.
minorTickPlacement: Defines whether the minor ticks appear on the inside, outside, or center of the line that represents an axis.
minorTickLength: Defines the length of each minor tick.
axis.title: Axis Title
Defines the title text for this axis. This text appears as an axis title label.
axisStrokeStyle: Defines the stroke style of the line that represents this axis.
axisStrokeWidth: Defines the stroke width of the line that represents this axis.
axisStroke: Defines the color of the line that represents this axis.
verticalAxisTitleAlignment: Controls axis label orientation. You might want to select Flipped Vertical if this axis is on the right side of your chart.
labelAlign:
For a vertical axis, determines whether the labels are aligned vertically to the top, middle, or bottom of the major ticks.

For a horizontal axis, determines whether the labels are aligned to the left, center, or right of the major ticks.
dgDataProvider: Specifies the table that this series uses as the data source.
inverted:
Controls whether this axis is inverted.

True
The smaller values appear at the top if this axis is vertical, or the right if it is horizontal. For a category axis, the top values in the table appear at the top or right of the axis.

On
The smaller values appear at the bottom or left of the axis. For a category axis, the top values in the table appear at the bottom or left of the axis.
dgAutoAdjust: Defines whether the axis range and ticks intervals are determined automatically based on the data feeding the chart.
displayName: Defines the display name of this series. You can choose to have this name appear in your interface, for example in datatips.
title: Title
stroke: Defines the stroke for this element.
fill: Defines the fill for this element.
strokeStyle: Defines the line style of the stroke for this element.
strokeWidth: Defines the width of the stroke line for this element.
placement:
For a vertical axis, defines whether the axis is positionined on the left or the right of the chart.

For a horizontal axis, defines whether the axis is positioned on the top or the bottom of the chart.

For a scale track, defines whether the track is positioned on the inside, outside, or center of the circle or line that defines the scale.
labelsColor: Defines the font color used for the labels along an axis.
formatString: Defines the format used for the axis labels. For example, a datetime axis might use the string "MM/dd/yyyy", and a number axis might use the string ",##0.00". See here for a complete list of formats.
maximum: Defines the highest number on the scale.
minimum: Defines the lowest number on the scale.
majorTicksCount: Defines the total number of major ticks along the scale.
percentRadius: Defines the radius of the circle that defines the scale, as a percentage of either the width or height of the container, whichever is larger.
angleTo: Defines the start angle of the circular scale. A value of zero indicates the top of the circle. Valid values are between −180 and 180.
angleFrom: Defines the end angle of the circular scale. A value of zero indicates the top of the circle. Valid values are between −180 and 180.
minorTickStrokeWidth: Defines the stroke width of each minor tick.
minorTickStroke: Defines the stroke color of the minor ticks.
offsetRight: Defines the distance between the right side of a linear scale and the container bounds.
offsetLeft: Defines the distance between the left side of a linear scale and the container bounds.
scaleType: Specifies whether the shape of the scale is defined by a circle or a straight line.
showRange: Specifies whether the component includes an option to choose a starting date/time and ending date/time.
showYear: Specifies whether the component includes an option to choose a calendar year.
showMonth: Specifies whether the component includes an option to choose a calendar month.
showRelative: Specifies whether the component includes an option to choose a date range relative to the current date.
showWeek: Specifies whether the component includes an option to choose a week beginning on Sunday and ending on Saturday.
showDay: Specifies whether the component includes an option to choose a day.
firstDow: Defines the day of the week that appears in the leftmost column of the calendar.
dowNames: Defines the day of the week names that appear on the calendar, as a comma-separated list of 7 values. The first value is mapped to Monday and the last value to Sunday, regardless of the currently selected First Day of Week. Must be 7 values in order for defined names to take effect.
monthNames: Defines the month names that appear on the calendar, as a comma-separated list of 12 values. The first value is displayed for January, and the last is displayed for December. Must be 12 values in order for defined names to take effect.
yField: Specifies the table column that is mapped to the y-axis for this series.
xField: Specifies the table column that is mapped to the x-axis for this series.
radius: Defines the radius of each item on this component.
maxCharLength: Specifies the maximum number of characters allowed in this text component.
letterSpacing: Specifies the horizontal spacing between letters. If null, the default spacing for the selected font is used.
wordWrap: Defines whether overflow text wraps. Mulitline must be enabled for this property to take effect.
verticalAlign: Defines whether the content in this component is positioned at the top, middle, or bottom of the container.
textAlign: Defines whether the content in this component is left-justified, centered, or right-justified.
fontSize: Defines the font size for this component. If the font size value is set to Auto, the text scales to occupy the size of the component.
minFontSize: Defines the minimum font size for this text component. This property is only applicable when text size is set to Auto.
maxFontSize: Defines the maximum font size for this text component. This property is only applicable when text size is set to Auto.
lineHeight: Specifies the vertical spacing between lines. If 0, the default spacing for the selected font is used.
text: Sets or reflects the string that appears in the Text component.
autoSize: Defines whether the Page Include inherits the sizing properties of its .dg5 file, for example a width that is a set number of pixels.
scrollbarStyles.thumb.background: Defines the fill of the thumb in the scrollbars on this container.
scrollbarStyles.thumb.border: Defines the stroke color of the thumb in the scrollbars on this container.
scrollbarStyles.thumb.borderStyle: Defines the line style of stroke on the thumb in the scrollbars on this container.
scrollbarStyles.thumb.borderWidth: Defines the weight of the stroke on the thumb in the scrollbars on this container.
scrollbarStyles.track.background: Defines the fill of the track in the scrollbars on this container.
scrollbarStyles.track.border: Defines the stroke color of the track in the scrollbars on this container.
scrollbarStyles.track.borderStyle: Defines the line style of stroke on the track in the scrollbars on this container.
scrollbarStyles.track.borderWidth: Defines the weight of the stroke on the track in the scrollbars on this container.
selectedIndex:
Sets or returns the index of the selected item in this container.

The first item has an index of 0.

The value −1 deselects all items.

If Multi-Select is enabled and multiple items are selected, comma-separated values are returned.
symbol: Specifies the symbol to be used when iterating the rows of the linked table.
keepEqualPaddings: Links all four padding editors so that their values are equal.
paddingRight: Defines a number of pixels of space between the right container boundary and the rightmost edge of the content. Negative numbers are not allowed.
paddingLeft: Defines a number of pixels of space between the left container boundary and the leftmost edge of the content. Negative numbers are not allowed.
paddingBottom: Defines a number of pixels of space between the bottom container boundary and the bottommost edge of the content. Negative numbers are not allowed.
paddingTop: Defines a number of pixels of space between the top container boundary and the topmost edge of the content. Negative numbers are not allowed.
vScroll:
Defines scrolling behavior on this element.

Off
Scrolling always disabled.

On
Scrolling always enabled. The track appears even if the content does not overflow.

Auto
Scrolling automatically gets enabled when content overflows.
hScroll:
Defines scrolling behavior on this element.

Off
Scrolling always disabled.

On
Scrolling always enabled. The track appears even if the content does not overflow.

Auto
Scrolling automatically gets enabled when content overflows.
clipContent:
Defines the handling of content that overflows this container.

True
All overflowed content is clipped and is not visible.

False
All overflowed content is visible and responds to mouse events.
layout:
Defines how elements are positioned within this container.

Absolute
Elements positioned freely.

Horizontal
Elements positioned in order horizontally left to right.

Vertical
Elements positioned in order vertically top to bottom.
alignContent:
Defines positioning of the columns and rows containing wrapped elements within this container.

Flex-start
Elements positioned at the start of the container.The rows are packed against the top edge, or the columns are packed against the left edge.

Flex-end
Elements positioned at the end of the container.The rows are packed against the bottom edge, or the columns are packed against the right edge.

Center
Elements positioned at the center.The rows or columns are packed together around the center of the container.

Space-between
Elements positioned such that there are equal amounts of space in between them (when multiple elements exist). The rows or columns are positioned against both edges, with equal space between them.

Space-around
Elements positioned such that there is an equal amount of space surrounding them (where multiple elements exist). The rows or columns are positioned with equal space between them, and space along both edges equal to half of the space between two rows or columns.

Stretch
Elements are stretched to fit the parent container.The rows or columns stretch to fit the parent container.
alignItems:
Defines vertical positioning of all elements within this container.

Flex-start
Elements positioned on the top. Elements are packed against the top edge.

Flex-end
Elements positioned on the bottom. Elements are packed against the bottom edge.

Center
Elements positioned at the center. Elements are packed together around the vertical center.

Space-between*
Elements positioned such that there are equal amounts of space in between them (when multiple elements exist). Elements are distributed with the top element flush against the top edge, the bottom element flush against the bottom edge, and equal space between the items.

Space-around*
Elements positioned such that there is an equal amount of space surrounding them (where multiple elements exist). Elements are distributed with equal space between them. The space at the top and bottom of the container equals half of the space between two adjacent items.

Baseline**
Baseline of all elements aligned to the baseline of the parent container.

Stretch**
Elements are stretched to fit the parent container. Elements stretch vertically to fit the parent container. The elements must have Autosize enabled in the direction that they stretch.

*Only available when Layout property is set to Vertical
**Only available when Layout property is set to Horizontal
justifyContent:
Defines horizontal positioning of all elements within this container.

Flex-start
Elements positioned on the left. Elements are packed against the left edge.

Flex-end
Elements positioned on the right. Elements are packed against the right edge.

Center
Elements positioned at the center. Elements are packed together around the horizontal center.

Space-between*
Elements positioned such that there are equal amounts of space in between them (when multiple elements exist). Elements are distributed with the left element flush against the left edge, the right element flush against the right edge, and equal space between the items.

Space-around*
Elements positioned such that there is an equal amount of space surrounding them (where multiple elements exist). Elements are distributed with equal space between them. The space at the left and right of the container equals half of the space between two adjacent items.

Baseline**
Baseline of all elements aligned to the baseline of the parent container.

Stretch**
Elements are stretched to fit the parent container. Elements stretch horizontally to fit the parent container. The elements must have Autosize enabled in the direction that they stretch.

*Only available when Layout property is set to Horizontal
**Only available when Layout property is set to Vertical
shadows: Attaches one or more shadows to this component.
borderStyle: Defines the line style of stroke for this component.
borderWidth: Defines the weight of the stroke line for this component.
border: Defines the stroke for this element.
background: Defines the fill for this element.
calCacheSymbol: Specifies whether to cache the callout symbol after it has been loaded the first time.
calVisible: Returns whether the callout is currently visible. For example, a mouse-over callout is visible only when the user mouses over the component.
calGrayOutComp: Defines whether the callout’s target becomes inactive and faded when the modal callout is displayed.
calModalFill: Specifies the background fill that appears when a modal callout is visible.
calHideIfOver: Determines whether the callout disappears when the user mouses over the callout.
calHide: Hides the callout. You can bind data or properties to this button, or click it as part of a recorded action.
calShow: Shows the callout. You can bind data or properties to this button, or click it as part of a recorded action.
calAnimation.duration: The duration of the callout display animation in seconds.
calStrokeWidth: Defines the stroke weight of the static callout’s bond.
calStrokeType: Defines the stroke type for the static callout’s bond.
calY: The Y Offset of a callout is the vertical distance from the top edge of the callout to the top edge of its target. You cannot manually set the Y Offset if the position of the callout is set as relative.
calX: The X Offset of a callout is the horizontal distance from the left edge of the callout to the left edge of its target. You cannot manually set the X Offset if the position of the callout is set as relative.
calRelTarget: Specifies whether the callout’s relative position (X and Y offsets) and size are relative to the callout's target component or to the page.
calloutSymbolId: Specifies the symbol to use for the callout. If the symbol is in this project, enter the name of the symbol. To use a symbol from another project in your library, enter the full path to that symbol.
rotateY: Defines a 3-D rotation along the y-axis. The value is an angle in degrees.
rotateX: Defines a 3-D rotation along the x-axis. The value is an angle in degrees.
rotate: Defines a 2-D rotation. The value is an angle in degrees.
cursor: Defines which cursor to show when mousing over this element. Only works when the Mouse Enabled property is true for both the element and its parents.
mouseEnabled: Defines whether this element responds to mouse events.
!label: Defines the display name of this component. This name appears in the Outline and breadcrumbs in DGLux.
flexShrink:
Specifies how much this element will shrink relative to the rest of the flexible items inside the same container. A value greater than zero indicates that this component will shrink to counteract insufficient space. The amount that it will shrink depends on its flex-shrink factor and the sum of all the flex-shrink factors assigned to items in the container.

For more information on flexible items go to: http://bocoup.com/weblog/dive-into-flexbox/
flexGrow:
Specifies how much this element will grow relative to the rest of the flexible items inside the same container. A value greater than zero indicates that this component will grow to absorb extra space. The amount that it will grow depends on its flex-grow factor and the sum of all the flex-grow factors assigned to items in the container.

For more information on flexible items go to: http://bocoup.com/weblog/dive-into-flexbox/
bottom:
In absolute layout, sets the bottom edge of this element to a distance above or below the bottom edge of its parent container.

In vertical or horizontal layout, sets the bottom edge of this element to a distance above or below its normal position.

A value of Auto positions the bottom edge of this component in its normal position.
right:
In absolute layout, sets the right edge of this element to a distance to the left or right of the right edge of its parent container.

In vertical or horizontal layout, sets the right edge of this element to a distance to the left or right of its normal position.

A value of Auto positions the right edge of this component in its normal position.
top:
In absolute layout, sets the top edge of this element to a distance above or below the top edge of its parent container.

In vertical or horizontal layout, sets the top edge of this element to a distance above or below its normal position.

A value of Auto positions the top edge of this component in its normal position.
left:
In absolute layout, sets the left edge of this element to a distance to the left or right of the left edge of its parent container.

In vertical or horizontal layout, sets the left edge of this element to a distance to the left or right of its normal position.

A value of Auto positions the left edge of this component in its normal position.
active: The Active property sets or returns whether the animation is currently running.
mode:
Determines the selection mode for the component.

Day
The user can select one day.

Week
The user can select one week. Selecting any date selects a week that includes that date. The week selected starts on a Sunday and ends on a Saturday, regardless of the currently selected First Day of Week.

Month
The user can select one month. Selecting any date selects its entire calendar month.
path: Specifies the relative or absolute URL of the .dg5 file to be used as a Page Include. This lets you use other .dg5 files as components within this file. To specify a file, either type a URL in the field, click the folder to specify a path, or drag a .dg5 file from the Project panel to the field.
opacity: Defines opacity of this component. If this component is a group or container, all elements inside are affected.
tilingOpt:
The Tiling/Scaling property determines whether the image tiles or scales within its container.

No Tiling
The image does not tile. An image larger than its container is clipped.

Tiling
The image tiles to fill the container either horizontally, vertically, or both horizontally and vertically.

Scaling
The image scales to the size of the container.
tilingOpt.tiling:
When Tiling is selected, this property determines whether the image tiles horizontally, vertically, or both horizontally and vertically.

Repeat
The image tiles horizontally and vertically.

Repeat Horizontally
The image tiles horizontally only. One row of tiles appears.

Repeat Vertically
The image tiles vertically only. One column of tiles appears.

When Scaling is selected, this property determines how the image scales when its container size changes.

Contain
The image scales while maintaining its aspect ratio. Part of the container might be empty.

Cover
The image scales to fill the container while maintaining its aspect ratio. Any part of the image that overflows the container is clipped.

Stretch
The image stretches to cover the container. The image’s aspect ratio is not maintained.
tilingOpt.angle: If Repeat Horizontally or Repeat Vertically is selected, changing this value causes tiles to repeat along an angle. Valid values are between −45 and 45.
tilingOpt.hAlign:
The Horizontal Alignment property determines how images or tiles are horizontally aligned.

Left
The leftmost edge of the image or tiles is justified to the left container boundary.

Center
The image or tiles are horizontally centered.

Right
The rightmost edge of the image or tiles is justified to the right container boundary.
tilingOpt.vAlign:
The Vertical Alignment property determines how tiled images are vertically aligned.

Top
The topmost edge of the image or tiles is justified to the top container boundary.

Middle
The image or tiles are vertically centered.

Bottom
The bottommost edge of the image or tiles is justified to the bottom container boundary.
gradient:
Defines the colors for a gradient fill, for example for a heat map or a scale track. To add colors, click below the track in the dialog. To delete colors, right-click on them in the dialog.

For a heat map, the left color indicates the lowest intensity, middle colors indicates medium intensity, and the right color indicates the highest intensity.
field: Defines the table column that contains the pie chart series data that determines wedge size.
data: Specifies the table for the repeater to use as the data source.
loop:
The Loop property determines whether the animation sequence is repeated.

True
As soon as it is complete, the animation starts again.

False
The animation happens once, and then the image defined for the image component is displayed.
color: Defines the font color for this component.
label.label: Label
daterange.format:
Defines the date format used by the component, as a date format string — for example, "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ss".

See date formatting help here.
daterange.nextRange: Returns the next chronological date range after the currently selected date range.
daterange.thisRange: Returns the currently selected date range.
daterange.previousRange: Returns the previous chronological date range before the currently selected date range.
daterange.next: Changes the currently selected value to the next chronological value. For example, if January 2016 is selected, this action changes the selection to February 2016.
daterange.previous: Changes the currently selected value to the previous chronological value. For example, if January 2016 is selected, this action changes the selection to December 2015.
daterange.duration: The duration of the currently selected date range, in milliseconds.
daterange.rangeDelimiter: Specifies the delimiter used between the start date and end date of the range.
getNode.name: Name
text.isHTML: Defines whether the string in this text component is treated as HTML, and HTML tags are parsed. Does not parse advanced HTML tags such as URLs.
text.isAdvancedHTML: Defines whether the string in this text component is treated as HTML, and all HTML tags are parsed, including URLs.
text.editable: Defines whether the user can edit the text in this text component at runtime by clicking into it.
text.multiline:
Defines whether this text component has multiline capability. Hold Alt+Enter to insert a line break.

True
Line breaks are recognized.

False
Line breaks are ignored. All text is displayed on a single line.
img.!numFrames: The Total Frames is the number of frames in the animation, not including the image. This is a read-only property, thus changing it manually does nothing. Add frames by clicking the Add button.
img.frameIndex: The Frame is the index of the frame currently displayed in the animation. The image at the URL defined for the image component is 0, the topmost frame in the animation sequence is 1, and so on.
img.intervalMillis: The Interval is the length of time that each frame is displayed, in seconds.
img.isAnimator: The Frame Animator property determines whether the image component animates through a specified list of frames. The image defined for the image component is only displayed when the animation is not active, unless it is also defined as an animation frame.
img.frames: The Frames are the paths to each of the frames in the animation sequence. Click Add to add frames, and then specify an image path for each frame.
img.reverse:
The Reverse property determines whether the animation frames are displayed in reverse.

True
The topmost frame in the Property Inspector appears first in the animation sequence.

False
The bottommost frame in the Property Inspector appears first in the animation sequence.
img.breakApart: Separates an SVG into its component vectors to allow you to edit an SVG within DGLux.
iframe.scrolling: Specifies whether scrolling is enabled on the IFrame component. If this is disabled, then content that overflows the component is clipped.
video.controls: Specifies whether video controls are shown to the user.
video.autoplay: Defines whether the video starts playing automatically when the video player element is loaded on the page.
video.play: Plays the video. You can bind to this button, or click it as part of a recorded action.
video.pause: Pauses the video. You can bind to this button, or click it as part of a recorded action.
video.stop: Stops the video. You can bind to this button, or click it as part of a recorded action.
video.restart: Restarts the video. You can bind to this button, or click it as part of a recorded action.
video.volume: Changes the video player’s volume. You can bind to this property, or modify it as part of a recorded action.
map.mapControls: Defines whether to show map controls, allowing the user to manipulate the map.
map.trafficLayer: Defines whether to show the Google Maps Traffic Layer on the map.
map.mapType:
Defines the type of Google Map to be displayed in the component.

Roadmap
The default road map view.

Satellite
Google Earth satellite images.

Hybrid
A mixture of road map and satellite images.

Terrain
A physical map based on terrain data.
map.latField: Defines the column in your table that contains latitude data.
map.lngField: Defines the column in your table that contains longitude data.
Google_Map.symbol: Defines the symbol to be used as a location marker. If the symbol is in this project, enter the name of the symbol. To use a symbol from another project in your library, enter the path to that symbol.
Google_Map.data: Defines the table from which latitude and longitude data for location markers can be determined.
heatMap.showLegend: Defines whether to show a simple legend in the heat map component.
heatMap.falloff: Defines the percentage of each heat map item that is covered by the highest intensity color for that shape. The specified inner portion of the shape is covered by the color representing the intensity of the data point. If falloff is less than 100%, then the outer portion of the shape blends from the color of this intensity value to the color of an intensity value of zero.
calendar.selectedDays: Sets or returns the currently selected date range as a comma-separated list.
calendar.noSelectFutureDate: Determines whether it is possible for the user to select future dates. If Selection Mode is set to Week or Month, the user can select the current week or month even if it contains future dates.
calendar.prevArrowSymbol:
Defines the text or the glyph used for the previous month button.

You can find more information on glyphs here.
calendar.nextArrowSymbol:
Defines the text or the glyph used for the next month button.

You can find more information on glyphs here.
calendar.currentMonth: Sets or returns the month of the current calendar page.
calendar.currentYear: Sets or returns the year of the current calendar page.
daterangePicker.buttonFontSize: Defines the font size for buttons within the component.
daterangePicker.buttonBackground: Defines the fill for buttons within the component that are not currently active (selected) or moused-over.
daterangePicker.buttonBackgroundActive: Defines the fill for active (selected) buttons within the component.
daterangePicker.buttonBackgroundOver: Defines the fill for moused-over buttons within the component.
daterangePicker.buttonBorder: Defines the border color for all buttons within the component.
datagrid.defaultCellKeepEqualPaddings: Links all four padding editors so that their values are equal.
datagrid.sortOrder:
Defines whether the data is sorted in ascending or descending order.

To change whether the data is treated as strings or numbers when sorted, open the dataflow for the data grid component and edit the sort block.
datagrid.sortColumn: Defines which column to use to sort the data, using the column name. Only works if the column has the Sortable property enabled.
chart.innerRadius: Defines the radius for the blank area in the center of the pie chart. This blank area is useful for creating multilevel pie charts and doughnut charts.
scaleTicks.ticksPlacement: Specifies whether the ticks are positioned on the inside, outside, or center of the circle or line that defines the scale.
scaleTicks.majorTickStroke: Defines the stroke color of the major ticks.
scaleTicks.majorTickStrokeWidth: Defines the stroke weight of each major tick.
scaleTicks.majorTicksPercentLength: Defines the length of each major tick, as a pixel value or a percentage. For circular scales, the percentage is a portion of the circle’s radius. For linear scales, the percentage is a portion of the container width.
scaleTicks.minorTicksCount: Defines the number of minor ticks between each consecutive pair of major ticks.
scaleTicks.minorTicksPercentLength: Defines the length of each minor tick, as a pixel value or a percentage. For circular scales, the percentage is a portion of the circle’s radius. For linear scales, the percentage is a portion of the container width.
scaleLabels.showMinMaxOnly: Defines whether the labels for the minimum and maximum of the scale are the only two labels that appear. This property overrides the Labels Count property.
scaleTrack.percentStartThickness: Defines the thickness of the scale track at its start, as a pixel or percentage value. For circular scales, the percentage is a portion of the circle’s radius. For linear scales, the percentage is a portion of the container width.
scaleTrack.percentEndThickness: Defines the thickness of the scale track at its end, as a pixel or percentage value. For circular scales, the percentage is a portion of the circle’s radius. For linear scales, the percentage is a portion of the container width.
pieSeries.radialStroke: Defines the stroke color for the edges between wedges. To edit the inner and outer circles of the pie chart, use the Fill and Stroke properties for the series.
pieSeries.radialStrokeWidth: Defines the stroke weight for the edges between wedges. To edit the inner and outer circles of the pie chart, use the Fill and Stroke properties for the series.
pieSeries.radialStrokeStyle: Defines the stroke type for the edges between wedges. To edit the inner and outer circles of the pie chart, use the Fill and Stroke properties for the series.
pieSeries.calloutStroke: Defines the stroke color for the wedge callout lines.
pieSeries.calloutStrokeWidth: Defines the stroke weight for the wedge callout lines.
pieSeries.calloutStrokeStyle: Defines the stroke type for the wedge callout lines.
pieSeries.colorField:
Specifies the table column that contains data from which to determine wedge colors. The following formats are supported:

  • #EEE — any shortened, three-digit hexadecimal color string, including the # symbol.
  • #FF00FF — any hexadecimal color string, including the # symbol.
  • rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5) — any RGBA color string, including "rgba" and the parentheses.
You can also specify colors in the Property Inspector by expanding Wedge Fills.
gridlines.gridDirection: Defines which gridlines are displayed in the plotting area of the chart. You can choose to have horizontal only, vertical only, both, or none.
gridlines.horizontalAlternateFill: Defines the second of two fills that alternate in the plotting area between horizontal gridlines.
gridlines.horizontalFill: Defines the first of two fills that alternate in the plotting area between horizontal gridlines.
gridlines.horizontalStroke: Defines the stroke color for horizontal gridlines.
gridlines.horizontalStrokeWidth: Defines the stroke width for horizontal gridlines.
gridlines.horizontalStrokeStyle: Defines the stroke style for horizontal gridlines. A stroke weight greater than 0 overrides a stroke style of None.
gridlines.verticalAlternateFill: Defines the second of two fills that alternate in the plotting area between vertical gridlines.
gridlines.verticalFill: Defines the first of two fills that alternate in the plotting area between vertical gridlines.
gridlines.verticalStroke: Defines the stroke color for vertical gridlines.
gridlines.verticalStrokeWidth: Defines the stroke width for vertical gridlines.
gridlines.verticalStrokeStyle: Defines the stroke type for vertical gridlines. A stroke weight greater than 0 overrides a stroke type of None.
gridlines.plottedAreaX: Returns the view x-coordinate at the left edge of the plotted area. This is a read-only property, so changing it manually does nothing.
gridlines.plottedAreaY: Returns the view y-coordinate at the top edge of the plotted area. This is a read-only property, so changing it manually does nothing.
gridlines.plottedAreaWidth: Returns the width of the plot area in pixels. This is a read-only property, so changing it manually does nothing.
gridlines.plottedAreaHeight: Returns the height of the plot area in pixels. This is a read-only property, so changing it manually does nothing.
